M|coding|conflicts: []
M|coding|- TypeScript strict mode where applicable
M|coding|- No `any` types unless absolutely necessary — add a comment explaining why
M|coding|- Prefer explicit return types on all functions
M|coding|- Use `const` by default; `let` only when reassignment is required
M|coding|- Keep functions small and single-purpose
M|coding|- Max 30 lines per function; extract if longer
M|coding|- Name functions after what they return, not what they do internally
M|coding|- No side effects in pure functions
M|coding|- Never swallow errors silently
M|coding|- Always log error ctx, not just the error message
M|coding|- Use typed errors where possible
M|coding|- Comment the why, not the what
M|coding|- If code needs a comment to be understood, consider simplifying it first
M|coding|- Never leave TODO comments without a ticket reference
M|coding|- One concern per file
M|coding|- Keep files under 200 lines; split if larger
M|coding|- Co-locate tests with implementation files
M|coding|- All brand changes go to `dev` branch — never commit directly to `main`
M|coding|- Commit messages: `type(scope): short description` (feat, fix, chore, docs)